latestPosts.caption:
Feeling rather Pooh Bear esque 🤰🏻

I need to admit defeat with this tank, this is the last time I can wear it, it’s feeling a bit like shape wear and bump needs a bit more wriggle room these days 😂 I’m taking this as my sign to get myself a couple of basics like tanks and tees to help see my through the next few months. 

I’m loving these Raey jeans, the gathered waistband fits under bump perfectly 🙌🏻 I’m actually wearing them more now than I did before.

latestPosts.caption:
AD | Who knew I’d be this excited over handles and hinges but here we are…I can’t wait to get these fitted on our new doors and show you the final look.

I struggled to find the perfect brass ironmongery which matched some existing brass hardware we have and was a design we loved, I didn’t want to compromise. Then I found @ironmongeryexperts who couldn’t have been more helpful, they listened to my requirements and did everything they could to help me select the right pieces. They put me onto these pieces made by @carlislebrass and I’m over the moon with them.

If you want the exact details, comment below and I’ll send you all the product codes you need to get your hands on these straight to your inbox. 

#Brassdoorhardware #knurleddoorhandle #Carlislebrass #brushedbrass #doorhardware #DIY #finishingtouches #ironmongery #satinbrass

I picked up these under bump jeans a few weeks back, they have an adjustable elastic waistband which is very handy. 

The long sleeve tshirt is an oversized top I already had which I can still get away with wearing 🙌🏻

latestPosts.caption:
I have recently been looking to add some shorter jackets into my wardrobe. I spotted this knitted bomber and really liked the relaxed look. And the gold snap button detail, and the fact it also has pockets was a winner!

I wore it as a jacket over the weekend and it was warm enough to do this, I also think it would make a good layer too when it gets really really cold. 

I’m planning to wear it next with white tailored trousers, and a grey tee. Or grey trousers…I haven’t got any but I reckon I need some! I think the options are endless for ways to wear this jacket tbh. 

PR @sezane
